  <h1>About</h1>
  <p class="lede">Senior software engineer with 8+ years building and operating backend systems. I share how real systems behave, AI in practice, and the engineering and product judgment behind good decisions.</p>

  <h2>What I do</h2>
  <p>I build reliable services with clear contracts, strong observability, and practical tooling. My focus is production systems: how they work, how they fail, and how to debug them. Most of what I find worth writing about lives after a design leaves the whiteboard — under retries, overload, concurrency, and partial failure.</p>

  <h2>How I think about the work</h2>
  <p>Seniority shows up in anticipated consequences, not in knowing more patterns. The questions that matter are usually about what happens twice, late, partially, or during recovery — and whether a technically valid design is still operationally responsible.</p>
  <p>The work is also not purely technical. Staying calm and structured during an incident, communicating risk before it becomes a surprise, writing documents that age well, and mentoring people earlier in the path are part of how engineering judgment becomes useful to a team. Mentorship, for me, is part of seniority: the highest-value help is usually a better question, not a handed-over answer.</p>

  <h2>Engineering areas</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>APIs &amp; services</strong> — contracts, performance, migrations</li>
    <li><strong>Data &amp; search</strong> — PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Elasticsearch</li>
    <li><strong>Reliability &amp; observability</strong> — SLOs, metrics, logs, traces</li>
    <li><strong>Developer tooling</strong> — automation, developer experience, CI</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Stack</h2>
  <p><strong>Languages</strong> — Ruby, Go, Java, Python</p>
  <p><strong>Infrastructure &amp; data</strong> — PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Elasticsearch, Redis, Aerospike, Kafka, Kubernetes</p>
  <p><strong>Observability</strong> — Prometheus, Grafana, Datadog, OpenTelemetry</p>

  <h2>Principles</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Clarity over cleverness</li>
    <li>Measure impact and make it observable</li>
    <li>Design for on-call: idempotency, backpressure, timeouts</li>
    <li>Prefer small, reversible steps</li>
    <li>Prefer boring technology that scales</li>
    <li>Prefer fast feedback loops</li>
    <li>Prefer documents that age well</li>
  </ul>

